HOW TO FIND US
At Hidden Cypress Farm, we are located in the heart of the beautiful Florida panhandle. Our private and gated farm is the perfect location for an unforgettable vacation. Whether you want to cut your own Christmas tree during the season, or enjoy the miles of walking and golf cart trails, fishing, bird watching, and wildlife viewing, we have something for everyone.Located near Falling Waters State Park and Florida Caverns State Park, our campground is the perfect home base for your next adventure. Equfina float trips are also available nearby, providing endless opportunities for outdoor fun.We can't wait to see you at Hidden Cypress Christmas Tree farm and private Campground!

Experience the Beauty of Nature at Hidden Cypress farm LLC, Christmas tree farm and private Campground
Welcome to Hidden Cypress Farm LLC, Christmas Tree Farm and private Campground, where you can experience the beauty of nature in a private and gated farm. Cut your own Christmas Tree during the season, Weekend of Thanksgiving until we are out, relax in our private campground with full hook ups, 50amp service, water, sewer, shower, and laundry facilities. Enjoy the warmth of a fire ring while having a picnic on our tables. Take a stroll or a golf cart ride through miles of our walking trails with sightings of various wildlife and bird watching. You can even go fishing in our pond. With our proximity to the beach, Falling Waters State Park, Florida Caverns State Park, and Econfina float trips, your adventure never ends. Come and join us!
Private Farm
Our private farm is your very own oasis where you can get away from it all and enjoy the tranquility of nature. With acres of land to explore, you're sure to find your own slice of paradise. Relax and unwind in our private campground with full hook ups, 50amp service, water, sewer, and shower facilities. You can also enjoy the warmth of a fire ring while having a picnic on our tables. Take a stroll or a golf cart ride through miles of our walking trails and enjoy sightings of various wildlife and bird watching. You can even go fishing in our ponds!
